added.title: Kryponite
added.description: When Robin explains that knowing your weakness makes you a better superhero, Starfire journeys to find hers.

added.title: Thumb War
added.description: As the other Titans engage in an all out thumb wrestling war, Starfire tries to broker peace.

added.title: Toddler Titans...Yay!
added.description: Control Freak thinks the Titans' humor is too juvenile for their time-slot, so he ages them down to a preschool show.

added.title: The Matchmaker
added.description: Gumball catches Darwin gazing wistfully at a photo of Teri on Elmore Plus and secretly enlists Carrie to help bring them together. But when they can't make Darwin and Teri's love blossom naturally, they decide to make it happen supernaturally.

added.title: The Box
added.description: The Wattersons receive an unmarked package in the mail. To distract themselves from the urge to open it they all take turns to imagine what it might contain. To Mom it could mean financial freedom, to Gumball it could mean superpowers; to whoever it's actually for, it means they're not getting their package.

added.title: The Console
added.description: When Gumball is given a cursed videogame console, Elmore becomes trapped inside a fantasy RPG world. Gumball, Darwin and Anais have to battle their way through town, unraveling the secrets of their new virtual reality. But they'll have to level up if they're going to stand any chance against the mysterious final boss.

added.title: The Ollie
added.description: When Darwin asks Gumball to teach him how to skate, Gumball makes sure he covers every aspect of the skating lifestyle from wearing the right gear, using the right terms and choosing the right board. But when Darwin finally gets his wheels rolling, he realizes there might be one important aspect of skating Gumball hasn't taught him.

added.title: The Catfish
added.description: When Gumball and Darwin realise Grandpa Louie has no friends on Elmore Plus, they feel bad so they create one called Muriel. However when Granny Jojo finds out Louie has been spending time online with another 'woman', Muriel not existing isn't going to stop her from being destroyed.

added.title: Under the Overpass
added.description: Craig and his friends travel to find honeysuckle in the creek but discover a whole new part of the creek.

added.title: The Invitation
added.description: Craig and his friends are invited to an exclusive tea party with delicious desserts, if they can last to the end of the party.

added.title: Vulture's Nest
added.description: Craig and his friends start a band, but Craig is haunted by a frightening nightmare.

added.title: Kelsey Quest
added.description: Kelsey accepts a quest from the Elders of the Creek, but is she ready for her terrifying opponent?

added.title: JPony
added.description: JP decides to follow his heart and tries to join the Horse Girls.

added.title: Sheep Bears
added.description: The Bears get jobs as sheep herders on an idyllic farm.

added.title: Ice Bear's Pet
added.description: Ice Bear attempts to keep a giant owl-monster secretly as a pet.

added.title: Dragon Pests
added.description: The Bears and Squatter Otter crash a couple's swanky pad while they're out of town.

added.title: No Land, All Air!
added.description: The Bears find themselves in a world of dog fighting planes and floating airships.

added.title: Tooth Fairy Tech
added.description: In order to earn enough money to buy a house, the Bears work as tooth fairies.

added.title: The Bad Guy Busters
added.description: Izzy wants to play a superhero game and is willing to do whatever it takes to get the others to see it through.

added.title: That's a Wrap
added.description: Duncan goes on a mission to scare Courtney during a field trip to the museum.

added.title: Tiger Fail
added.description: Gwen refuses to be pressured into choosing an ice cream flavor that she does not want.

added.title: A Ninjustice to Harold
added.description: Harold's world is turned upside down when Beth becomes the class ninja.

added.title: Having the Timeout of Our Lives
added.description: Owen forms a special bond with Duncan after having loads of fun with him during their timeouts.

added.title: One Hit Wonder
added.description: Apple & Onion can't bear to work another day in their dead end jobs at the dollar store but as always, money is the issue. If only there was a way they didn't have to worry about money any more.

added.title: A Matter of Pride
added.description: Apple & Onion's jobs have become too demeaning. They decide to put their foots down. It's a matter of pride.

added.title: Eyesore a Sunset
added.description: Art is subjective and Apple and Onion agree to let that get between them.

added.title: For Queen and Country
added.description: Onion has an unexpected and impossible new love interest. Off to England then.

added.title: Petri
added.description: Apple and Onion must get back to their apartment to put the lid on their petri dish.

added.title: This One Goes to 11
added.description: During one last stop by a toy store before Ben, Gwen, and Grandpa Max's maiden voyage across the Atlantic, Ben runs into an old bully, Kevin 11, who now has new powers. He's able to transform into aliens just like Ben, such as the bootleg doppelganger of Cannonbolt. Wreckingbolt!

added.title: Rath of Con
added.description: Back stateside, Ben can't get into a cat cosplay competition, Top Tail, without a costume of his own; but when he goes Rath, a new cat-like alien with an attitude, Ben's newfound wild side quickly becomes much more than he bargained for.

added.title: Poles Apart
added.description: A trip to the South Pole goes upside down when Team Tennyson lands on the North Pole instead, but Ben quickly discovers the culprits: Solar & Polar Twain, magnetically-powered scientists who want to hold the world ransom by threatening to reverse Earth's magnetic poles!

added.title: Show Don't Tell
added.description: Ben, Gwen, and Grandpa Max arrive at a Native American national park to witness the Ayasha Plinths, an ancient Stonehenge-like rock formation. But when the sinister sorcerer Hex arrives, Ben must battle against a beast Hex magically made out of huge rocks!

added.title: Welcome to Zombozo-Zone!
added.description: During medieval times, Team Tennyson must fight to remember that they're not in the past at all, but actually at a Renaissance-esque faire, where "King Zombozo" has hypnotized its guests into thinking they live in the past!

added.title: Hunted
added.description: Three alien bounty hunters are hot on Ben's trail. But one of them is a secret agent trying to make sure the Omnitrix does not fall into evil hands.

added.title: Tourist Trap
added.description: While messing with the World's Largest Rubberband Ball at a tourist trap, Ben accidently releases some mischievous electrical creatures.

added.title: Kevin 11
added.description: After a big argument with Max, Ben rebels by going out on his own in the Big Apple and makes friends with Kevin 11, who has plans for the Omnitrix.

added.title: The Alliance
added.description: As Fourarms, Ben works to thwart an armored truck robbery by a tough female gang leader named Joey, who delivers a disturbing message from Vilgax.

added.title: Last Laugh
added.description: Ben's fear of clowns emerges at an unfortunate time when our heroes stumble upon a wicked circus with a psychic vampire clown named Zomobozo.

added.title: Rad Monster Party
added.description: Ben and Rook enlist the help of intergalactic smuggler Rad Dudesman to fly them through the Anur System, the home of the monstrous aliens!

added.title: Charmed, I'm Sure
added.description: Still stranded on the monster planet Anur Transyl, Ben and Rook reluctantly team up with Charmcaster to take on Zs' Skayr.

added.title: The Vampire Strikes Back
added.description: Ben, Rook, and Rad Dudesman come face to face with the evil Lord Transyl, a vampire-like alien who can make anyone his loyal slave! (Introducing new Ben alien, Whampire.)

added.title: Catfight
added.description: The princesses Looma and Attea are at odds over who gets to marry Ben!

added.title: Collect This
added.description: Ben finally meets the ones responsible for his intergalactic TV show, and the actor who makes Ben 10 more famous than Ben himself!

added.title: Steven the Sword Fighter
added.description: Pearl tries to teach Steven the art of sword-fighting using a holographic version of himself.

added.title: Lion 2: The Movie
added.description: Steven and Connie try to ride the Lion to the movie theater but Lion has other ideas.

added.title: Beach Party
added.description: After a battle damages Fish Stew Pizza, Steven throws a cookout at the Temple to mend the relationship between Pizza family and the Crystal Gems.

added.title: Rose's Room
added.description: Steven's desire for some alone time unlocks a new room in the Temple that answers his every wish.

added.title: Coach Steven
added.description: After seeing Gamet and Amethyst fuse together into the powerful Sugilit - Steven becomes determined to get super strong.

added.title: Finn the Human
added.description: After chasing the Lich through the portal, Finn and Jake meet a wishmaster named Prismo.

added.title: Jake the Dog
added.description: Jake and Prismo watch from the portal as the Ice King's crown makes Finn more and more powerful.

added.title: I Remember You
added.description: Ice King and Marceline share a tender and revealing few moments reminiscing.

added.title: Reign of Gunters
added.description: The Gunters go on a rampage against the Ice King and the citizens of Ooo!

added.title: The Lich
added.description: A visit from the Lich King shines some light on some of Ooo's secrets.

added.title: Return of Mordecai and the Rigby's
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby want to win an air conditioner in a battle of the bands.

added.title: Bad Portrait
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby have to re-paint Benson's portrait for a party.

added.title: Video 101
added.description: Eileen, Mordecai, Rigby, and CJ want to make a music video for Eileen's filmmaking class.

added.title: I Like You Hi
added.description: Mordecai has to tell C.J. that his text was auto-corrected to say "I like you."

added.title: Play Date
added.description: Mordecai has to watch Thomas.

added.title: Beep
added.description: To help combat bummer feelings, Unikitty's installed Bad Vibe detectors throughout the castle. But soon, annoying beeping detectors fill the halls, and they can't find the source of the bad vibes or shut off the sound! It would seem someone's not owning up to being in a bad mood.Will the friends figure out who is secretly a Negative Nancy, or will they lose their mind to beeping madness?

added.title: Delivery Effect
added.description: Unikitty and gang have ordered some delicious Thai food for dinner.  Unfortunately the wait for the delivery is proving too much, time itself seems to have slowed down. In an effort to get the food their faster the gang utilizes Dr. Fox's time machine, which causes big problems and really hurts Father Time's feelings.

added.title: Lazer Tag
added.description: When the Score creeper traps Unikitty and the gang in his laser tag arena the gang must defeat the house team or be imprisoned forever.

added.title: Trapped in Paradise
added.description: Unikitty and the gang have crashed on a fabulous island. It's really nice and no one wants to leave until Richard convinces them that they need to return to the Kingdom and deal with their responsibilities. Unfortunately every attempt to escape the island is sabotaged. Now they must find the culprit to ensure their return home.

added.title: Prank War
added.description: When Master Frown starts a prank war with UniKingdom, the friends are ready to strike back. But Unikitty doesn't really understand pranks, thinking they're too mean. Can the friends help Unikitty comprehend a proper goof and win the prank war with Frown? Or will they be forced to suffer his tricks without retaliation and admit defeat?

added.title: A Very Special Blossom/Daylight Savings
added.description: A Very Special Blossom: When the Professor wants an expensive gift for Father's Day, Blossom makes the mistake of taking what she can't afford instead of giving him a gift from the heart./Daylight Savings: The Powerpuff Girls are exhausted in school from saving Townsville past their bedtime. What will happen to their town when the girls are put on a curfew?

added.title: Slave the Day/Los Dos Mojos
added.description: Slave The Day: The girls save Big Billy's life, and he is forever indebted. But how will they get this bumbling fellow out of their way so they can save the world?/Los Dos Mojos: After she gets knocked on the head, Bubbles wakes up thinking she is Mojo Jojo. What is the world going to do with two evil Mojos?

added.title: Beat Your Greens/Down N' Dirty
added.description: Beat Your Greens: When Broccoli Aliens from space invade Townsville, it's up to the Powerpuff Girls and all the children of Townsville to take a bite out of crime. Down N' Dirty: When Buttercup refuses to take a bath, the town kicks her out. But Buttercup decides to stick with her stink until her favorite thing is taken away from her.

added.title: Dream Scheme/You Snooze, You Lose
added.description: Dream Scheme: The Sandman would like a little rest so he puts the world to sleep. The girls must battle him in his dreams to get things back to normal./You Snooze, You Lose: When the Amoeba Boys find Mojo's plan to destroy the Powerpuff Girls, the girls unwittingly help them build a machine for their own destruction.

added.title: Birthday Bash/Too Pooped to Puff
added.description: Birthday Bash: It's the girls birthday and some special presents have arrived from the girls' main enemies. Can they destroy these evil gifts without destroying their party?/Too Pooped to Puff: The girls become exhausted when the town begins to over use them. They go on strike and end up teaching the townspeople how to fend for themselves.

added.title: Frenemy
added.description: When the coolest girl in school befriends the girls, she charms them into becoming her accomplices in a series of adventurous crimes.

added.title: Once Upon a Townsville
added.description: When a dainty princess on a mission comes to Townsville, the girls must learn the superhero way isn't always the right way.

added.title: Man Up 2: Still Man-ing
added.description: When someone steals all the water in Townsville, it's up to the girls to race through the Townsville Wastelands to get it back.

added.title: Viral Spiral
added.description: When the Amoeba Boys wreak havoc on the internet, Bubbles has to hack her sisters in to stop them.

added.title: Bubbles of the Opera
added.description: When Bubbles gets a bad school photo, it sends her into an existential tailspin of darkness.

added.title: Private Lake
added.description: When the local lake is overcrowded with tourists, the Bears have fun at Charlie's private lake.

added.title: Lunch with Tabes
added.description: When Tabes's lunch gets stolen, Tabes launches a full investigation to find the culprit.

added.title: Road Trip
added.description: Chloe and the Bears take a road trip to see a meteor shower. Ice Bear, the only one licensed to drive, is put in charge, which becomes harder than he thought.

added.title: Summer Love
added.description: Panda goes on a mission to return a lost phone to the girl of his dreams.

added.title: The Kitty
added.description: After a mishap in the forest, the Bears lose their own home to dangerous animals.

added.title: Slumber Party
added.description: Clarence struggles to make a connection at an all-girls slumber party, leaving Sumo and Jeff at odds without Clarence as their "friendship buffer."

added.title: Nature Clarence
added.description: Clarence, Sumo and Jeff's nature hike veers off course courtesy of their under qualified, overwhelmed guide Josh, prompting Clarence to take the lead.

added.title: Average Jeff
added.description: Jeff suffers an identity crisis when a standardized test lands him in the lesser of the classes academic groupings.

added.title: Lizard Day Afternoon
added.description: Clarence and Sumo chase a lizard to unexpected rewards as Jeff jockeys for playing time on Belson's spectacular new gaming system.

added.title: The Forgotten
added.description: After Clarence and his indecisive classmate Brady are left behind at school, Brady is forced to tag along on Clarence's adventure home.

added.title: Trash Cat
added.description: Uncle Grandpa helps a cat who's afraid to take baths.

added.title: Uncle Grandpa's Odd-yssey
added.description: Uncle Grandpa and the gang must retrieve Tiger from the pound before she's adopted out.

added.title: Surprise Party
added.description: Mr. Gus and Belly Bag are throwing a surprise party for Pizza Steve, as long as  Uncle Grandpa doesn't spoil their surprise.

added.title: Late Night Good Morning With Uncle Grandpa
added.description: It's the Late Night Good Morning show with your host, Uncle Grandpa!

added.title: New Direction
added.description: Uncle Grandpa and the best directors in the business help a kid in need of acting lessons become a star.

added.title: I Am Okino
added.description: Inside one of the game zones, a Samurai named Okino faces a crisis of faith when he repeatedly fails to lead a series of Masters to victory, causing him to lose all hope, until some familiar ninja arrive.

added.title: The Glitch
added.description: In order to stop Unagami the ninja must obtain three Key-tanas, the first of which is hidden in the game zone Terra Kerana, one of Prime Empire's most dangerous game environments.

added.title: The Cliffs of Hysteria
added.description: While being chased by Unagami's dreaded Red Visors the ninja must climb the 'Cliffs of Hysteria', however, they make a startling discovery: Unagami is converting players into energy cubes in order to build a portal into the real world!

added.title: The Maze of the Red Dragon
added.description: Still in the game zone Terra Kerana, the Samurai guide Okino has to choose between helping his allies the ninja, or obeying the evil orders of his Master, Unagami.

added.title: One Step Forward, Two Steps Back
added.description: When the ninja learn that the only way to acquire the second Key-tana is by winning a dangerous race in Terra Technica they'll have to find some racing cars in unexpected ways.

added.title: Dangerous Dealings/The Hunter Returns
added.description: Dangerous Dealings: The Awesome Brawler's have become aware of a growing number of adults with illegal Baku-brawling devices. But where are they all coming from? Shun decides to take things into his own hands and sets up a "sting" operation to try to draw out the person selling the devices./The Hunter Returns: Lightning has been caught and locked up by an overly aggressive dog catcher! And to make things worse, he doesn't have his collar with Baku-balls. At the compound where he's being held, he runs into an old foe.  It's up to these two enemies to team up and escape their captor.

added.title: Farewell, Phantom Thief
added.description: After being exposed as a phantom thief in the Bakugan battle league, the Awesome Brawlers are concerned about Ajit, but have no idea of his whereabouts. Dan is particularly affected by Ajit's disappearance and sets out to find him to get some answers./Ajit is out to set right all the wrong doings of his phantom thief past. When he attempts to break into a museum to return artifacts, his mentor Storm is waiting for him. A Bakugan brawl breaks out between two when Storm rolls out his new Bakugan: Cimoga.

added.title: The Awesome Brawlers and Haavik/First Fusion! Drago and Tretorous
added.description: The Awesome Brawlers and Haavik: It's the Haavik Show! Haavik shows up unexpectedly at the practice field and proposes he and Dan play a little game. The Awesome Brawlers have never seen this man before, but they sense something is odd about him. Regardless, when Haavik strokes Dan's ego, there's no way he's backing down from this challenge./First Fusion! Drago and Tretorous: With his back against the wall, Dan tries flipping the script on Haavik by challenging him to a game of his own - a Bakugan Brawl. If Dan wins, then Haavik will have to set him, and the other Awesome Brawler's free.

added.title: The Puppet Awesome Brawlers/The Return of Sophie
added.description: The Puppet Awesome Brawlers: The Awesome brawlers go to see Benton Dusk to tell him about the Fusion Bakugan and ask him if he knows anything about this character: Haavik. However, the meeting takes an unexpected twist when Haavik decides to crash it./The Return of Sophie: A video has surfaced showing Toshi using an illegal Baku-Brawling device! Shun has his hands full when Sophie starts making trouble for Kazami Holdings, accusing them of illegally exploiting Bakugan.

added.title: Wynton's Reality Show/Bakugan Soccer
added.description: Wynton's Reality Show: Lia has had it with Wynton's pranking, but little does she know Wynton is in for a taste of his own medicine. A prank goes too far, and Wynton finds himself in a real-life nightmare with a rampaging Bakugan!/Bakugan Soccer: The Awesome Brawlers and their Bakugan decide to have a game of Bakugan Soccer! The intensity ramps up when Pepe, his teammates and a mysterious coach show up for a little fun. It will take major teamwork for the Awesome Brawlers Bakugan to defeat this rowdy bunch.

added.title: Lago privado
added.description: Cuando el lago de la zona está repleto de turistas, los Osos se divierten en el lago privado de Charlie.

added.title: Almuerzo con Tabes
added.description: Cuando alguien se roba el almuerzo de Tabes, él organiza una investigación a fondo para hallar al culpable.

added.title: El viaje
added.description: Chloe y los osos hacen un viaje en auto para ver una lluvia de meteoritos. Polar, el único que tiene licencia de conducir, está a cargo del manejo, lo cual se vuelve más difícil de lo que pensaba.

added.title: Amor de verano
added.description: Panda se embarca en una misión para devolverle a la chica de sus sueños el teléfono que perdió.

added.title: El gatito
added.description: Luego de un percance en el bosque, los Osos pierden su hogar en manos de unos animales peligrosos.

added.title: Yo Soy Okino
added.description: Dentro de una de las zonas de juego, un Samurai llamado Okino se enfrenta a una crisis de fe cuando no logra que los Maestros obtengan la victoria.

added.title: La Falla
added.description: Para detener a Unagami, los Ninjas debe obtener 3 Keytanas, la primera está escondida en Tierra Karana, uno de los entornos de juego más peligrosos.

added.title: Los Acantilados de la Histeria
added.description: Los Ninjas suben a los Acantilados de la histeria y descubren que Unagami convierte a los jugadores en cubos de energía para construir un portal.

added.title: El Laberinto del Dragon Rojo
added.description: Aún en la zona de juego de Tierra Karana, Okino tiene que elegir entre ayudar a sus aliados ninjas, u obedecer las órdenes de su Maestro, Unagami.

added.title: Un Paso Adelante, Dos Pasos Atras
added.description: La única manera de que los Ninjas obtengan segunda Keytana es ganando una carrera en Tierra Technica y tiene que conseguir autos de carreras para eso.

added.title: Bip
added.description: Para ayudar a combatir los sentimientos negativos, Unikitty ha instalado detectores de malas vibraciones en todo el castillo. Pero pronto, la molesta alarma de los detectores llena los pasillos, iy nadie puede encontrar la fuente de las malas vibraciones ni apagar el sonido! Parece que alguien no está reconociendo su propio mal humor. ¿Se darán cuenta los amigos de quién es la persona que guarda su negatividad en secreto, o perderán la cabeza por la locura de la alarma?

added.title: Efecto Entrega
added.description: Unikitty y su banda pidieron una deliciosa comida tailandesa para la cena. Por desgracia, la espera para la entrega se está haciendo demasiado larga y hasta el tiempo parece pasar más lento. En un esfuerzo por conseguir la comida más rápido, la banda utiliza la máquina del tiempo de la Dra. Fox, lo cual causa graves problemas y hiere profundamente los sentimientos del Padre Tiempo.

added.title: Lazer Tag
added.description: Cuando un villano atrapa a Unikitty y a la banda en su campo de disparos láser, deben derrotar al equipo local o quedar atrapados para siempre.

added.title: Atrapados en el paraiso
added.description: Unikitty y la banda aterrizaron de emergencia en una isla fabulosa. Todo es muy bonito y nadie quiere irse hasta que Richard los convence de que tienen que volver al Reino y asumir sus responsabilidades. Por desgracia, alguien sabotea cada intento de escapar de la isla. Ahora deben encontrar al culpable para asegurar su regreso a casa.

added.title: Guerra de Bromas
added.description: Cuando Master Frown comienza una guerra de bromas con el Unireino, los amigos están listos para contraatacar. Pero Unikitty no entiende bien las bromas, y piensa que tienen demasiada maldad. ¿Pueden los amigos ayudar a Unikitty a comprender una buena broma y ganar la guerra contra Frown? ¿O se verán obligados a sufrir sus bromas sin represalias y admitir la derrota?

added.title: Los Caza Chicos Malos
added.description: Izzqy quiere jugar un juego de superhéroes y está dispuesta a hacer lo que sea por ello.

added.title: Show de momias
added.description: Duncan sale en una misión para espantar a Courtney durante una excursión al museo.

added.title: Fallo de tigre
added.description: Gwen se niega a que la presionen para elegir un sabor de helado que no quiere.

added.title: Una ninja justicia para Harold
added.description: El mundo de Harold queda de cabeza cuando sus compañeros declaran que Beth es la verdadera ninja de la clase.

added.title: Bajo el Puente
added.description: Craig y sus amigos viajan para encontrar madreselva en el arroyo, pero descubren una parte completamente nueva del arroyo.
added.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

added.title: El castigo de mi vida
added.description: Owen forma un nexo especial con Duncan después de que ambos se divirtieran mucho durante sus castigos.

added.title: La Invitacion
added.description: Craig y sus amigos están invitados a una exclusiva merienda con deliciosos postres, si es que pueden quedarse hasta el final de la fiesta.
added.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

added.title: Nido de buitres
added.description: Craig y sus amigos forman una banda, pero a Craig lo atormenta una pesadilla aterradora.
added.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

added.title: La aventura de Kelsey
added.description: Kelsey acepta una misión de los Ancianos del Arroyo, pero ¿está lista para su aterrador rival?
added.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

added.title: J-Pony
added.description: JP decide seguir su corazón y trata de unirse a las Chicas Ecuestres.
added.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

added.title: Sidekicked to the Curb
added.description: When Bam is sent to take on Prank, Redbird is forced to hang back because The Joker's van is too dangerous! When Bam discovers that Redbird secretly tagged along, he's upset… until Redbird bails him out of a tight spot.

added.title: Keep Calm and Roll On
added.description: After Jestah's insults get the best of her, a short-tempered Bibi tries to not let the big-wheeled bully's words get to her so she can help Batgirl catch Harley.

added.title: Snow Cap
added.description: Pauleen Penguin hires The Looney Builders to build her a home in Looneyburg. Lola soon discovers they got the design wrong and the crew has to make adjustments.

added.title: Tweety-Go-Round
added.description: Tweety leads The Looney Builders in building a new merry-go-round at the park for the kids. His crane breaks down and his small size affects his ability to contribute to the build.

added.title: Picture Perfect Park Party/Sun Block
added.description: Hero Celebration Day is finishing with a slideshow of everyday heroes, that is, until the projector screen rips./Pretty Big City is cooling off with an ice slide in the park, but the situation gets slippery when the slide starts melting.

added.title: Roll Chickens, Roll!/Ramp Up, Up, And Away
added.description: Farmer MacBarm is hosting the Sunny Field Farm Chicken Roll, but the race gets off to a slow start when the chickens don't roll./Ranger Nat can't wait to see Pinecone's Comet, that is, until his telescope falls to the bottom of a cliff.

added.title: Mystery Boxcars
added.description: Kana is upset when she keeps running out of power, but a mystery scavenger hunt is just the thing to cheer her up.
added.originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

added.title: Super Screen Cleaners
added.description: Thomas pretends to be a hero to help ensure the movie screen Nia's delivering arrives clean and pristine.
added.originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

added.title: Overnight Stop
added.description: Percy feels anxious about spending a night away from home during an overnight delivery with Thomas and Nia.
added.originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

added.title: Gravity
added.description: Three, two, one, lift-off! On this mission to the moon, Blippi bounces around with Rocky the Moon Rock. Light as a feather they bound up and float back down, teaching Blippi all about gravity! One small step for Blippi, one giant leap for Blippi.

added.title: Honey
added.description: Blippi and FETCH shrink down and fly inside a very active beehive, where they meet Bijon, the fast-talking, fast-moving Worker Bee. With a talent for rhyming and making honey, Bijon rhymes her way through the sweet explanation of how delicious honey is made. What a very buzzy... erm...busy day!

added.title: Ocean
added.description: Blippi's trusty BlippiMobile safely transports him to a whole new underwater world! He dives into the sea, where he gets an ocean tour from a local resident, Jerry the Jellyfish. They swim through a huge kelp forest, explore the ocean floor and meet interesting underwater creatures along the way!

added.title: Planets
added.description: Three, two, one, Blast Off! The BlippiMobile becomes a spacecraft on this mission to find out which planets are in the solar system! Merry the Meteor is the perfect host as Blippi is escorted through space and receives a guided tour of all the planets and their positions from the sun.

added.title: Mountain
added.description: Blippi and TABBS head off on an icy adventure and fly up the side of Mt. Everest, the world's tallest mountain! They are joined by Betty the Yeti who is climbing to the top of the mountain in search of the ultimate snack - fresh snow!

added.title: Wheels on the Bus
added.description: Ella and Mummy take the big red bus to Lellobee farm, where she meets Mia and the rest of the team!

added.title: Wash Your Hands, Scrub That Soap
added.description: Ella is getting muddy. Mei comes out with a plate of dumplings, but Ella's hands are dirty!

added.title: Yes Yes Vegetables Song - Healthy Habits!
added.description: Baby Izzy doesn't like vegetables - until they sing a song with her!

added.title: The Sandman Is Coming
added.description: Daffy thinks the Sandman is a monster that throws sand in children's eyes.

added.title: Some Assembly Required
added.description: Bugs gets a new toy with assembly required and has to learn to follow instructions.

added.title: All Washed Up
added.description: Taz decides he doesn't like taking a bath.

added.title: Did Not! Did Too!
added.description: Bugs and Lola temporarily decide that they don't want to be friends any longer.

added.title: Tea & Basketball
added.description: Sylvester wants to play tea with the girls while Lola wants to play basketball with the boys.

removed.title: Pintura dolorosa
removed.description: Leshawna inventa una pelea con globos llenos de pintura para ver quién va al parque de diversiones con ella.

removed.title: Ninjago Confidencial
removed.description: De vuelta en la ciudad de Ninjago, Zane y Pixal salen a las calles para encontrar a Milton Dyer, y descubren que las cosas no son lo que parecen…

removed.title: Bananas y Queso
removed.description: Duncan está decidido a evitar que el dúo Banana y Queso se presente en la guardería.

removed.title: Aterrizaje mocoso
removed.description: A Beth se le atascan los muebles del diorama de Courtney en la nariz y Courtney tiene que recuperarlos antes de que llegue el juez del concurso de dioramas.

removed.title: Ninos vergonzosos
removed.description: Owen teme perder a su mejor amigo Noah que se va a una escuela militar.

removed.title: No sin mis choco-lletas
removed.description: Noah intenta rescatar los chocolates que Owen olvidó afuera.

removed.title: Piloto Siete
removed.description: Mientras los Ninjas se preparan para la carrera Cinco Billones por Hora, Lloyd conoce a la Piloto Siete quien puede tener la clave de la victoria.

removed.title: El Padre Prodigo
removed.description: Zane, secuestrado por el Mecánico mientras Pixal interroga a Milton Dyer para obtener información sobre cómo cerrar el Primer Imperio.

removed.title: Carrera Cinco Billones por Hora
removed.description: Los soldados de Unagami, los Visores Rojos, finalmente descubren la ubicación secreta del garaje de Scott y atacan a los Ninjas.

removed.title: Detenerse, Caer y Girar
removed.description: Los Ninjas no han ni llorado la pérdida de sus amigos  caídos cuando ya deben entrar a la locura de Tierra Domina.

removed.title: And Then There Was Ben
removed.description: Professor Paradox unites the good Bens from across all dimensions to take on Vilgax, Eon, and the evil Bens in the ultimate showdown!

removed.title: Weapon XI Part 2
removed.description: The Rooters have seemingly turned Kevin and the Amalgam kids against Ben. Can Rook and Gwen help him overcome the opposition and escape the Null Void?

removed.description: Rook is under the influence of Fistrick's "bro" essence, and starts to act like a bro. Can he and Ben infiltrate an alien fight club to claim the Golden Fist? (Introducing Slix Vigma, alien promoter.)

removed.title: Universe vs. Tennyson
removed.description: Ben gets dragged into intergalactic court by the other Celestialsapiens (Alien Xs) for recreating the universe (back in "So Long and Thanks for All the Smoothies").

removed.title: And Then There Were None
removed.description: Vilgax and Eon team up to wipe out every Ben in every dimension!

removed.title: Cough It Up
removed.description: Psyphon and a gang of bounty hunters are after Argit, who is in possession of a dangerous weapon!

removed.title: Weapon XI Part 1
removed.description: Kevin and Argit attempt to warn the amalgam kids about the Rooters intentions meanwhile Ben, Rook, and Gwen set off to find Kevin and land themselves in the Null Void!

removed.title: The Rooters of All Evil
removed.description: Meet the Rooters, the Black Ops wing of the Plumbers from the Null Void. They've come looking for someone close to Ben, and they mean business!

removed.title: The Vengers
removed.description: Billy Billions, Kangaroo Kommando, and Captain Nemesis team up to take down Ben, and claim his place as protector of Bellwood?!?

removed.title: Blukic and Driba Go to Area 51
removed.description: A mysterious Galvan arrives and demands Blukic and Driba to give back a super powerful weapon needed to stop a threat to Earth.

removed.title: No Monsters Scared of the Dark
removed.description: The Baby Pumpkins are scared of the dark as they go to the halloween party!

removed.title: Bam's Upgrade
removed.description: Feeling neglected after being passed over on missions, Bam asks MOE to install experimental upgrades to curry Batman's favor. But, when Bam's new powers are stronger than he can control, Batman - and the mission - are suddenly in danger!

removed.title: Snowflake
removed.description: It's an icy day, and a very cold Blippi heads to the sky to find out how snowflakes are made. Way up high in the winter clouds he helps Mimi, an athletic dust particle, achieve her goal to build up enough ice crystals and transform into a unique and awesome snowflake. Way to be original Mimi!

removed.title: Fruit & Vegetables
removed.description: On the hunt to discover the difference between fruits and vegetables, Blippi finds himself as a contestant in a community garden game show! Game show host Slim Cucumber quizzes Blippi on his knowledge of fruits and vegetables. Will Blippi know the answers?

removed.title: Chocolate Factory
removed.description: Blippi's love for chocolate makes him wonder "How are chocolate bars made?" They head into a chocolate factory to find out, get a tour from Bard the Chocolate Bar, and FETCH gets a close-up look at the chocolate-making process!

removed.title: Australia Kangaroo
removed.description: Blippi stumbles across a Kangaroo Crossing sign in Australia and wonders "How high can a kangaroo jump?" His new kangaroo mate Rudy is happy to demonstrate, challenging Blippi to a hopping race around the famous sandstone monolith Uluru. Can Blippi jump as high as a kangaroo?

removed.title: Play Day
removed.description: When the Looney Builders build themselves a playground, Daffy gets so excited about his section that he takes all the supplies for himself.

removed.title: Accidents Happen Boo Boo Song
removed.description: Ella falls over, but Heidi the Horse teaches her to get right back up again!

removed.title: The Joke is on Thomas
removed.description: When Thomas and Percy's plan to surprise Diesel goes awry, the two friends still manage to cheer up Diesel... just not in the way they expected!
removed.originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

removed.title: Redbird's Bogus Beach Day
removed.description: Redbird gets excited when he learns that Batman and Robin are taking him and Bam for a drive up the coast! But when the Joker and his van Prank show up unexpectedly and ruin Redbird's beach day plans, Bam helps him realize that even though things didn't go exactly as planned, they still had a great day!

removed.title: The Treasure of Treetop Woods/Zee Makes an Amazing Maze!
removed.description: Ranger Nat's hike turns to adventure when he finds a treasure map. The only problem is that he can't read it./Zee and MacBarm are setting up their corn maze with the help of Zee's Zee Mobile… that is, until it breaks down inside the maze.

removed.title: Lost and Found
removed.description: When Thomas helps Nia make a delivery to the beach in Norramby, he insists he knows a shortcut and leads the way! But it turns out his memory isn't as good as he… remembered.
removed.originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

removed.description: When all the trains but Thomas get deliveries, he's left to spend the day alone. With the help of an old boxcar and a battered beachball... an adventure unfolds.
removed.originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

removed.title: Yip Yip, Book Book!/Stick to It!
removed.description: It's the Pretty Big All City Read and Izzy and Barb are ready, that is, until all the books go missing!/Pretty Big City finds itself in a sticky situation when the factory starts spewing super sticky slime everywhere!

removed.title: Bath Song
removed.description: Ella gets covered in mud so she goes into Mei's farmhouse to have a bath.

removed.title: Band Together
removed.description: The babies learn about music and improvise their own orchestra.

removed.title: Smash House
removed.description: The Looney Builders learn that Taz accidentally destroyed his house, so they set out to build him a new one that's smash-proof.

removed.title: Sneeze
removed.description: What is making Blippi sneeze? What makes anyone sneeze? Blippi shrinks down and flies up a nose to find out! A very mischievous piece of pollen demonstrates how to make a sneeze happen, resulting in Blippi himself getting blown away by a giant sneeze!

removed.title: Business as Unusual
removed.description: Bugs and Daffy open competing lemonade stands.

removed.title: The Harder They Fall
removed.description: Bugs is embarrassed to admit he doesn't know how to skate.

removed.title: War of the Weirds
removed.description: Marvin the Martian comes to visit, and the babies learn to accept differences.

removed.title: Taz You Like It
removed.description: Taz discovers pratfalls get him laughs and attention.

removed.title: Moor Fogg
removed.description: Team Tennyson goes international in the Omni-Copter and the first stop is for a hike in the Scottish Highlands, but the weather isn't just bad, it's foggy, and that means one thing and one thing only: the return of The Fogg!

removed.description: Team Tennyson checks out a Samurai Museum in Tokyo, where Ben is too impatient to wait out the Calligraphy experience for the more exciting sounding Samurai one. But when a dangerous Samurai sword is stolen from the exhibit, Ben must take on its thief, the new Big Bad in town, the Forever Knight.

removed.title: Speechless on the Seine
removed.description: While in Paris, France, Ben catches Zombozo robbing the Louvre, but when Zombozo hypnotizes Ben to remain speechless, Ben must navigate a foreign land like a mime in order to stop the criminal clown and his travelling circus.

removed.title: King of the Castle
removed.description: Ben, Gwen, and Grandpa Max next travel to Castle Bishopbrook to visit a distant relative who's royalty, but when Ben encounters a "ghost" at the haunted home, it turns out to actually be his new rival, Kevin 11, throwing even more twisted aliens his way: Thornblade, Undertow, and Dark Matter!

removed.title: Big in Japan
removed.description: During a tour of the Japanese Robotics Museum, Ben finds hero-gone-wrong Tim Buktu "trying to save" Tokyo from a Dragon. Has Tim finally turned over a new leaf, or is this just another one of his half-baked plans to play the part of hero?

removed.title: Snots Landing
removed.description: Beth gets Courtney's diorama furniture stuck up her nose and Courtney needs it back before the diorama contest judge arrives.

removed.title: Paint That a Shame
removed.description: Leshawna creates a paint balloon fight to decide who gets to come with her to an amusement park.

removed.description: Owen fears he's about to lose his BFF Noah to a gifted military school.

removed.title: Bananas & Cheese
removed.description: Duncan is determined to stop the musical duo Bananas & Cheese from coming to the daycare.

removed.title: Not Without My Fudgy Lumps
removed.description: Noah tries to rescue the chocolates Owen forgot outside.

removed.description: Eliminated from the Bakugan Battle League, Ajit is airlifted by drone to a massive cargo ship in the middle of Tokyo Bay. Now that he's on board the cargo ship, he must rescue Dan and Drago, and stop whoever is sabotaging the Battle League. Dan and Ajit investigate the mysterious cargo ship that the eliminated brawlers and Bakugan are being held on. Dan races to track down Drago, but along the way runs into a familiar face.

removed.title: Shun and Lightning/Premonition of a Storm
removed.description: Shun and Lightning: Shun and Lightning are on the hunt for a rare Tumpee, when they run into McQ! With all the devices related crimes happening in Los Volmos, Shun decides to investigate to try to get to the bottom of McQ's nefarious dealings./Premonition of a Storm: After a run in with McQ, Shun and Lightning find themselves in a little bit trouble.
